name: In the Still of the Night
Music Box Dancer
comments: Initially issued as the "B" side of "The Poet and I" in 1978. Became a hit after a copy of the single was sent to a pop station in Canada and the station flipped the record over after being unable to figure out why they were sent a copy. Following the success of the song in Canada, the song was issued as a single with "The Poet and I" on the B side in the US. The song was also a huge hit in the US and peaked at #3 in early May of 1979.
